 artefacts. Jana Scholz discusses why they can appear alive to us.  afunded by Potsdam Graduate School  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAnthropomorphism in art. 0aAnthropomorphism in literature. 0aClothing and dress in art. 0aFantasy in art. 0aSubculture. 4aAgency. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aAnthropomorphismus. 4aArtefakte. 4aFotografie. 4aGestalt. 4aInszenierung. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKunst. 4aKunsttheorie. 4aLiteratur. 4aMensch-Ding-Interaktion. 4aMode. 4aWahrnehmung. 4aÄsthetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aAgency.  aAnthropomorphism.  aArt.  aArtefacts.  aCultural Studies.  aFashion Studies.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aHuman-thing-interaction.  aLiterature.  aPerception.  aPhotography.  aShape.  aStaging.  aTheory of Art.2 aPotsdam Graduate Schoolefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.14361/9783839448175zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839448175423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783839448175.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019